<P>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>The Florida Bar</H1>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../../gif/devault.gif">
The Florida Bar is an organization consisting of attorneys and judges licensed
to practice law in the state of Florida. The current membership of The Florida
Bar is approximately 52,000; about 43,000 of which reside in the state.
The purpose of The Florida Bar is to provide services for both its membership
and the general public. For attorneys, The Florida Bar provides interpretations
of the Rules of Professional Conduct, administers Continuing Legal Education
(CLE) seminars and programs, publishes The Florida Bar News and The Florida
Bar Journal, and otherwise endeavors to maintain the integrity of The Bar
while assisting in the professional growth of its membership.<P>
For the general public, The Florida Bar administers a number of programs
aimed at improving the manner in which legal services are provided in the
state of Florida. Among these programs are the Fee Arbitration Program which
helps clients and lawyers resolve fee disputes, the Client's Security Fund
which compensates clients for losses due to misappropriation of funds by
errant Florida lawyers, and the Law Related Education Program which promotes
"legal literacy" among Florida's young people. The Florida Bar
also investigates the unlicensed practice of law, investigates complaints
made against attorneys, maintains the Florida Call-A-Law service which provides
recorded information on a variety of basic legal topics, and maintains a
public information office providing news releases, educational pamphlets,
and other promotional materials. <P>
The Florida Bar is headquartered in Tallahassee on a five-acre site just
three blocks from the capitol. The Florida Bar's other branch offices are
located in Miami, Tampa, Orlando, and Fort Lauderdale.<P>
<P>
The Florida Bar Center<BR>
650 Apalachee Parkway<BR>
Tallahassee, FL 32399-2300<BR>
(904) 561-5600<P>


<CENTER><H1>Local or Specialized Florida Bar Associations</H1></CENTER>

In addition to The Florida Bar, in which membership is mandatory, there
are a variety of local or specialized bar associations in which membership
is voluntary. The following is an abbreviated list of these bar associations.<P>

