<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>The Academy of Florida Trial Lawyers</H1>
The Academy of Florida Trial Lawyers (the Academy) represents more than
3,500 trial attorneys. As part of its mission, the Academy works in both
the legislative and public opinion arenas to protect constitutional rights,
to improve public safety, and defend the interests of accident victims.
The Academy is particularly active in the areas of automobile safety, drunk
driving, children's issues, professional malpractice, and the availability
of adequate and affordable insurance coverage.<P>
Among its services, the Academy provides information to print and broadcast
media regarding topics of current interest, legislative research and lobbying,
assistance to consumer and human service groups, public education and service
programs (such as the Speakers' Bureau, People's Law School, and Friends
of Guardian Ad Litem programs), and continuing legal education seminars.
<P>

The Academy of Florida Trial Lawyers<BR>
218 South Monroe Street<BR>
Tallahassee, FL 32301<BR>
Phone: (904) 224-9403<BR>
Fax: (904) 224-4254<P>

