<P>
<H1><CENTER>Appendix D: Florida Courts</CENTER>
</H1>
<HR SIZE=4 WIDTH=100% ALIGN=CENTER>

<P>
<STRONG><H1 ALIGN=CENTER>The Supreme Court of Florida</H1></STRONG>
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gif/supreme.court.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>The Supreme Court of Florida<BR>
Supreme Court Building<BR>
500 South Duval Street<BR>
Tallahassee 32399-1925<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR> (904) 488-0125<BR>
Library: (904) 922-5520</CENTER>
<P><HR SIZE=4 WIDTH=100% ALIGN=CENTER><P>
<STRONG><H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Florida District Court of Appeal</H1></STRONG>
<P>
<CENTER>Florida is divided into five appellate districts, each with a district court
of appeal</CENTER>
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../../gif/5courts.appeals.gif">
<P>

<STRONG>First District</STRONG><BR>
State of Florida<BR>
Courthouse<BR>
301 Martin L. King, Jr., Boulevard<BR>
Tallahassee, FL 32399-1850<BR>
Comprising the 1st, 2nd, 3rd, 4th 8th and 14th Circuits<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR> (904) 488-6151
<P>
<STRONG>Second District</STRONG><BR>
State of Florida<BR>
P.O. Box 327<BR>
1005 East Memorial Boulevard<BR>
Lakeland, FL 33802-0327<BR>
Comprising the 6th, 10th, 12th, 13th and 20th Circuits<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR> (941) 499-2290
<P>
<STRONG>Third District</STRONG><BR>
State of Florida<BR>
2001 South West 117 Avenue<BR>
Miami, FL 33175-1716<BR>
Comprising the 11th and 16th Circuits<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR> (305) 229-3200
<P>
<STRONG>Fourth District</STRONG><BR>
State of Florida<BR>
1525 Palm Beach Lakes Boulevard<BR>
P.O. Box 3315<BR>
West Palm Beach, FL 33402<BR>
Comprising the 15th, 17th and 19th Circuits<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR> (407) 697-7200
<P>
<STRONG>Fifth District</STRONG><BR>
State of Florida<BR>
300 South Beach Street<BR>
Daytona Beach, FL 32114<BR>
Comprising the 5th, 7th, 9th and 18th Circuits<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR> (904) 255-8600
<P><HR SIZE=4 WIDTH=100% ALIGN=CENTER><P>
<STRONG><H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Circuit Courts</H1></STRONG>
Florida is divided into 20 circuits, each with its own circuit court and
made up of one or several counties.
<P>

<STRONG>First Judicial Circuit</STRONG><BR>
(Escambia, Okaloosa, Santa Rosa, and  Walton Counties)<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR>	
(904) 436-5110 (Escambia)<BR>
(904) 689-5800 (Okoloosa)<BR>
(904) 623-0135 (Santa Rosa)<BR>
(904) 892-8115 (Walton)
<P>
<STRONG>Second Judicial Circuit</STRONG><BR>
(Franklin, Godsen, Jefferson, Leon, Liberty, and Wakulla Counties)<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR>	
(904) 653-8861 (Franklin)<BR>
(904) 875-8601 (Godsen)<BR>
(904) 997-3596 (Jefferson)<BR>
(904) 488-7534 (Leon)<BR>
(904) 643-2215 (Liberty)<BR>
(904) 926-3341 (Wakulla)
<P>

<STRONG>Third Judicial Circuit</STRONG><BR>
(Columbia, Dixie, Hamilton, Lafayette, Madison, Suwannee, and Taylor Counties)<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR>
(904) 758-1041 (Columbia)<BR>		
(904) 498-1200 (Dixie)<BR>
(904) 792-1288 (Hamilton)<BR>
(904) 294-1600 (Lafayette)<BR>
(904) 973-4176 (Madison)<BR>
(904) 364-3498 (Suwannee)<BR>
(904) 584-3531 (Taylor)
<P>
<STRONG>Fourth Judicial Circuit</STRONG><BR>
(Clay, Duval, and Nassau Counties)<BR>
Clerk's Office: <BR>	
